{{Quote|I left Canada around 20 years ago to travel around the world, ended up in Japan, and started in animation over there. It was excellent because it gave me this expertise really early on in my career that allowed me to move into the States.|Catherine Winder|<ref name="Georgia">Lupick, Travis. [http://www.straight.com/article-158377/clone-wars-galactic-task "Clone Wars proved a galactic task for production team."] [[Wikipedia:The Georgia Straight|''The Georgia Straight'']], [[August 21]], [[2008]]. Retrieved on [[2008]]-[[August 21|08-21]].</ref>}}
'''Catherine Winder''' was the [[Wikipedia:Executive producer|executive producer]] at [[Lucasfilm Animation]]. Since [[2007]], she oversaw the development and production on the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' and the [[2008]] [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)|film of the same name]] until she was replaced by [[Cary Silver]] during the production of the [[The Clone Wars: Season One|first season]] of the series.<ref name="Leading the Charge">{{SWArchive|url=theclonewars/news20091022.html|text=Leading the Charge: ''Clone Wars'' Producer Cary Silver}}</ref> Winder is a native of [[Wikipedia:Toronto|Toronto]], [[Wikipedia:Canada|Canada]] and began her film career in [[Wikipedia:Japan|Japan]], which she later said helped her in adopting [[Wikipedia:Anime|anime]] and [[Wikipedia:Manga|manga]] elements into the unique ''Clone Wars'' animation style.<ref name="Georgia" />

